-- TNK-BP Says Ex-Manager Took $13 Million Bribe, Kommersant Says
-- B y   I l y a   A r k h i p o v
-- 2012-08-21T05:05:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-21/tnk-bp-says-ex-manager-took-13-million-bribe-kommersant-says.html
TNK-BP, the Russian oil venture of
 BP Plc (BP/) , said a former logistics manager took $13 million in
bribes from companies he awarded transport contracts to,
Kommersant reported, citing a court claim by TNK-BP.  TNK-BP is seeking to freeze the assets in the U.S. held by
the manager, who filed his own claim against TNK-BP in a London
court last, the Moscow-based newspaper said today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Arkhipov in Moscow at 
 iarkhipov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net  